desktop-description =
    FreeSynergy Desktop is the graphical shell for the FreeSynergy platform.

    It provides the workspace with a CSS Grid-based layout: a header bar with
    branding and user menu, a collapsible sidebar for app navigation, a main
    content area, and a taskbar at the bottom. All FreeSynergy apps run inside
    the Desktop as embedded windows or launch as standalone windows.

    Built with Dioxus — the same codebase runs as a native desktop application
    (webview), as a web application (WASM), and in TUI mode for headless servers.

desktop-features =
    - CSS Grid workspace: header, sidebar, main area, taskbar
    - Window manager: open, minimize, resize, close app windows
    - Collapsible sidebar: 240px expanded, 48px icon-only
    - Taskbar with app launcher, system tray, and clock
    - Wallpaper support with theme integration
    - Offline-capable: works without internet after initial setup
    - Three rendering modes: desktop (webview), web (WASM), TUI
